title: For Sale:  1983 Crosman 6100 Challenger Olympic Style Air Rifle
postcontent:
Break action single shot .177 air rifle, 30 years old be looks almost brand new.  The stock has a couple minor dings, but the barrel and metal are all in great shape.  

This rifle was designed as a competition gun and was imported from Germany.  It was sold there as the Diana model 45, and it is still extremely accurate.  It's really fun to shoot, but I just don't shoot it enough to justify holding onto it.  

This would be an awesome gun for kids or adults looking to get into competition air rifle shooting, but not looking to spend 600 dollars or more for a gun alone, or even teaching your kid to shoot without breaking the bank on crazy ammo prices.  This air rifle isn't a toy bb gun!

The rifle features an adjustable trigger, a rear site that is adjustable for windage and elevation, and an adjustable front site as well.  It sits in a really nice monte carlo style stock, and has great balance and accuracy.

I will consider trades for firearms, and possibly accessories, but I'm not really looking for ammo and cash is always king.
